# Shadow Society — agent guidelines

This repo is the **Shadow Society** Next.js platform (not a generic starter to rebrand). Prefer product work in `src/components/shadow-society/` and the debate API client.

See also: `shadow-society-context.mdc` (sibling layout), `docs/COMPONENTS.md`, `docs/FONTS.md`.

## Product checklist

| Area | Where |
|------|--------|
| Brand & SEO | `src/app/layout.tsx` (`metadata`) — already Shadow Society |
| Env | `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` → `shadow-society-services` |
| Main UI | `src/components/shadow-society/` |
| Debate API | `src/data/api/server/debate.ts` |

## Agent behavior

- Extend **shadow-society** screens and cylinder-window components for product UI.
- Match existing patterns (`ServicesProvider`, debate client, `@/components/...` imports).
- Do not reintroduce template landing/auth as the primary product surface unless the user asks.
- When adding UI dependencies, isolate them in feature wrappers (easy to remove).
- Keep i18n keys in sync (`en` / `es`) if you touch message bundles.
